:"text","text":"When an action is committed, all of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"do_*"},{"text":" methods will run. If the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/undo()"},{"text":" method is used, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"undo_*"},{"text":" methods will run. If the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/redo()"},{"type":"text","text":" method is used, once again, all of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"do_*"},{"text":" methods will run.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here’s an example on how to add an action:","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before calling any of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"add_(un)do_*"},{"type":"text","text":" methods, you need to first call "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/createAction(name:mergeMode:backwardUndoOps:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Afterwards you need to call "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/commitAction(execute:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t need to register a method, you can leave ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/addDoMethod(callable:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/UndoRedo\/addUndoMethod(callable:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" out; the same goes for properties. You can also register more than one method\/property."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you are making an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorPlugi